column886: We always come when we are called
column887: We are prepared for any rhythm
column888: We should get some coffee… Because I'm liking you a latte.
column889: When we first met I couldn't get you out of my mind, now I can't get you out of my heart.
column890: When you walked in the door your beauty hit me so hard that I have a priapism from all the trauma.
column891: Whenever I'm near you, I undergo anaerobic respiration because you take my breath away.
column892: Where there is a pulse there is a chance.
column893: You breathe oxygen? We have so much in common.
column894: You give me premature ventricular contractions.
column896: You know, I've been highly trained to stick things into people…
column897: You look familiar. Did we have class together? I could have sworn we had chemistry.
column898: You make my dopamine levels all silly.
column899: You must be the one for me… Since my selectively permeable membrane let you through.
column900: You've got 206 bones in your body, want one more?
column903: Your calves must be aching. Because you've been back-marching through my mind all day.
